{
  "analysis": "Tooling is installed and video metadata shows 1280x720, 30fps, 190.1s. OCR of the 2s sample clearly shows the Zork start screen and prompt. Later sample extraction only produced frames up to 120s because requested timestamps beyond duration failed. We still need extract frames across the whole video, OCR the prompt/text regions, reconstruct the typed moves, and write /app/solution.txt. The next concrete step is to extract one frame per second and inspect OCR output to confirm screen layout and prompt behavior.",
  "plan": "Extract frames at 1fps into /app/work/frames, count them, and run OCR on the first 20 frames. This will show how the screen changes over time, where the prompt/input line is, and how commands appear. Then we can build a robust extraction script.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ffmpeg -hide_banner -loglevel error -y -i /app/video.mp4 -vf fps=1 /app/work/frames/frame_%04d.png; ls /app/work/frames | head -20; echo COUNT=$(ls /app/work/frames | wc -l)\n",
      "duration": 10.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom PIL import Image\nimport pytesseract, glob, os\nfor p in sorted(glob.glob('/app/work/frames/frame_*.png'))[:20]:\n    im=Image.open(p)\n    txt=pytesseract.image_to_string(im)\n    print('\\\\n====', os.path.basename(p), im.size, '====')\n    print(repr(txt)[:2000])\nPY\n",
      "duration": 3.0
    }
  ]
}
